      "writtenOn": "2017-11-20T17:09:21Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Are we ever going to load two instances of the same obj with different transformations? SceneObject abstraction currently packs too much data into one for that kind of thing (each associated loading an OBJ file, its transforms, shader program, etc etc)",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 97,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 97,
        "endChar": 60
      },
      "revId": "a00c9b8dab9a1dea59f96b4a8db23ebbefa35cbe",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "749fb840_ebb09134",
        "filename": "android/android-emu/android/virtualscene/Renderer.h",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 97,
      "author": {
        "id": 1233742
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-11-21T01:23:34Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "SceneObject is intended to be a container of an object with a transformation.  Take a look at the document I shared, currently it has a lot of functionality in it but the plan would be to split it out over time (when we have a need to do so).",
      "parentUuid": "c9cc336a_d00261a7",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 97,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 97,
        "endChar": 60
      },
      "revId": "a00c9b8dab9a1dea59f96b4a8db23ebbefa35cbe",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "ca4c0287_61f7a977",
        "filename": "android/android-emu/android/virtualscene/SceneObject.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 95,
      "author": {
        "id": 1235311
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-11-20T17:30:21Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "it doesn\u0027t seem like the shader compilation belongs in the renderer the way this is architected.  As far as I can tell it\u0027s only currently used by the scene object.  Can we just move the shader stuff into here?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 91,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 95,
        "endChar": 79
      },
      "revId": "a00c9b8dab9a1dea59f96b4a8db23ebbefa35cbe",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "1823209d_51250141",
        "filename": "android/android-emu/android/virtualscene/SceneObject.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 95,
      "author": {
        "id": 1233742
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-11-21T01:23:34Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "True, however I\u0027d like to eventually move rendering details out of SceneObject instead of into it.  Eventually instead of compiling shaders, I\u0027d like this to be a \"createMaterial()\" call which would return a Material container object, and not deal with shader compilation at all.",
      "parentUuid": "ca4c0287_61f7a977",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 91,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 95,
        "endChar": 79
      },
      "revId": "a00c9b8dab9a1dea59f96b4a8db23ebbefa35cbe",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "64d719a6_06b59ad7",
        "filename": "android/android-emu/android/virtualscene/SceneObject.cpp",
